### Power Rating

The rated power is the rate at which energy is used (power consumption) by a device when the device is operating at the rated potential difference across it.

For an electrical device rated 100 W, 220 V, it means that when a potential difference of 220 V is applied across the terminals of the device, the device dissipates 100 W of power.

